<item>
            <title>[SOLR-46] support for appended and invariant SolrParams in solrconfig.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-46</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;this patch would add support to StandardRequestHandler and DisMaxRequestHandler for specifying &quot;appends&quot; and &quot;invariants&quot; SolrParams in the solrconfig.xml, from the example config...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;         In addition to defaults, &quot;appends&quot; params can be specified&lt;br/&gt;
         to identify values which whould be appended to the list of&lt;br/&gt;
         multi-valu params from the query (or the existing &quot;defaults&quot;).&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
         &quot;invariants&quot; are a way of letting the Solr maintainer lock down&lt;br/&gt;
         the options available to Solr clients.  Any params values&lt;br/&gt;
         specified here are used regardless of what values may be specified&lt;br/&gt;
         in either the query, the &quot;defaults&quot;, or the &quot;appends&quot; params.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...functionality is largely reusable by any handler, via SolrPluginUtils.setDefaults.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
